name: pydelatin
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.2.6" %}
{% set name = "pydelatin" %}

package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 6b608b4881ef691b3062085d91fe0d46865679009eb4e3422fad9a379978c471

build:
  number: 1
  skip: true  # [py<36] [python_impl == 'pypy']
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
  host:
    - python
    - numpy
    - pybind11 >=2.5.0
    - glm
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}

test:
  imports:
    - pydelatin

about:
  home: https://github.com/kylebarron/pydelatin
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Python bindings to hmm for fast terrain mesh generation
  description: |
    A Python wrapper of hmm (of which Delatin is a port) for fast terrain mesh generation.
  doc_url: https://github.com/kylebarron/pydelatin
  dev_url: https://github.com/kylebarron/pydelatin

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - davidbrochart
    - kylebarron
